        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1970-09-07T09:48:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1970-09-07T09:48:00-05:00" n="205"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d205">
                <head>205. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassies in Switzerland, the United Kingdom, Israel, and
                        West Germany</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d205fn1">Source: National Archives, <gloss
                            target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 59, Central Files 1970–73, AV 12 <gloss
                            target="#t_US1">US</gloss>. Secret; Flash. Drafted and approved by
                            <persName corresp="#p_SJJ1">Sisco</persName> and cleared by <persName
                            corresp="#p_JUA1">U. Alexis Johnson</persName>. It was repeated to
                        Beirut and <gloss target="#t_USINT1">USINT</gloss> Cairo.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1970-09-07T14:48:00+00:00">September 7, 1970,
                        1448Z</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>146375. You should inform Government to which you accredited immediately of
                        <gloss target="#t_PFLP1">PFLP</gloss> demands as reported in Amman
                        4372.<note n="2" xml:id="d205fn2">Telegram 4372 from Amman, September 7,
                        1125Z, reported that the <gloss target="#t_PFLP1">PFLP</gloss> made five key
                        demands focused on releasing passengers in exchange for the release of
                        Palestinian prisoners held in Switzerland, Britain, West Germany, the United
                        States, and Israel. (Ibid.)</note> In view linkage of demands, it important
                    that any response to <gloss target="#t_PFLP1">PFLP</gloss> be made <pb
                        facs="0640" n="607" xml:id="pg_607"/> only after closest possible
                    consultation between governments principally concerned. We are in touch with
                    representatives of respective governments here in Washington, and important that
                    matter of any response be concerted here in Washington. Would appreciate your
                    requesting government to which you accredited to instruct their respective
                    Embassy to keep in closest concert with State Department so that this matter can
                    be considered.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RWP1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Rogers</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
